ik zu nehmen. Galbraith‘ Bücher und Reden fanden viel Resonanz, vor allem im Kontext der kritischen Betrachtung des neuen Wohlstands seit den 1960er Jahren. Warum fanden seine Worte so starken Widerhall? Welche Parteien und Gruppierungen waren an seinen Perspektiven interessiert und aus welchen Motiven? Die Analyse seiner Schriften und Korrespondenzen sowie seiner medialen und politischen Rezeption nimmt das Wirken Galbraith‘ – auf Basis bislang ungenutzter Quellen – neu in den Blick.  aThe Canadian-American economist John Kenneth Galbraith (1908–2006) is considered to be one of the most prolific economic and societal commentators of his time. Anne-Kristin von Dewitz examines his relationship to Germany from the 1940s onward and describes the influential impact he made as a public intellectual in the decades after the war against the backdrop of major societal and political upheavals.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomicszGermanyxPhilosophy. 4aBundesrepublik. 4aIdeengeschichte. 4aKalter Krieg. 4aUSA. 4aZeitgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century / Cold War.2bisacsh  aCold war.  aFederal Republic of Germany.  aUSA.  acontemporary history.  aintellectual history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831111077520 cprintz978311108619440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311110666340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111106663423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111106663/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_D